I want to sell/trade because I’m just not shooting it.  The range where I shoot has the rifle range about 75 yds from the pistol ranges so when I’m done shooting my pistols I have to put everything back in the car and drive down to the rifle range.
Price is $385 and I'd like to see an NCDL.

title: For Trade:  Tanfoglio/EAA Witness .45 LIKE NEW IN BOX W/ EXTRAS
postcontent:
STOP. READ THIS FIRST: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FIREARM TRADE OFFERS ONLY. NO EXCEPTIONS. I DO NOT WANT YOUR ILLEGAL DRUGS, MEDICAL MARIJUANA, TATTOOING SERVICES, QUESTIONABLE OR STOLEN ELECTRONICS DEVICES AND CELL PHONES, GAMING CONSOLES AND/OR ANY OTHER ITEM THAT IS NOT A FIREARM. SUSPICIOUS ACTIVITY/CORRESPONDENCE REGARDING THIS AD WILL BE REPORTED TO THE PROPER AUTHORITIES. I RESERVE THE RIGHT TO AT ANY TIME ARBITRARILY REQUIRE A WA STATE DRIVERS LICENSE, CONCEALED PISTOL LICENSE AND/OR A SIGNED BILL OF SALE OR TRADE. THANK YOU.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

I have a Tanfoglio Witness .45 auto for trade. Double/Single action, 10 round magazine capacity. This gun is incredibly accurate and has impressive ergonomics. Made by Tanfoglio in Italy and imported by EAA, these guns are used in match competition as an alternative to the single action 1911. This one has the proprietary anti-corrosive Wonder finish. According to the proof marks, this gun was made in 1999 and the serial number range falls outside the factory firing pin recall that applied to certain guns which had to be sent in for an upgrade. Aside from the soft rubber factory grips and the magazine floor plate, there isn't a piece of plastic on this gun-- it is built like a tank and is a breeze to field strip. It also has the desirable stronger, older style square-sided slide (Newer round slides and some square sided guns had issues with slides cracking, though primarily in 10mm and .40 chamberings). This is one of the harder to find older, problem-free guns before quality control issues started to crop up with newer ones on some online forums.

The gun has a very low round count and is like new in the original box with the manual and a blank warranty registration card (limited life-time factory warranty). It will include an Uncle Mike's holster with magazine pouch, a spare factory magazine and a trigger lock. It belonged to my late grandfather who didn't shoot it much and kept it in excellent condition.

I am interested in trading for a different pistol, preferably also in .45 ACP. I have found that I prefer the 1911 platform. Trade value is $550. I am open to a variety of different trades at this point, but a 1911 would be nice (Rock Island Armory, Remington R1 1911, Springfield Armory Mil-Spec). I'd really like an officer's model sized sub compact (Kimber pro-carry Ultra II, Colt MK IV or maybe an HK .45 USP Tactical, in which case I have a Beretta M92FS Inox, a Savage-Stevens 311 H series SxS double barreled shotgun that is hammer less with dual triggers, or a .50 Cal Spanish made Kentucky cap and ball pistol I could throw in to compensate for the difference in value.

The Tapco collapsible stock w/ pistol grip was designed for a stock Saiga, however the pistol grip can be removed so the stock can be used with an AK or converted Saiga. title: For Sale:  Custom Built Mauser Action. .30-06 Ackley Improved
postcontent:
This was my dad's rifle custom built by his Gunsmith at Capital Sports in Helena in the 90s. I don't know everything about it but this is what I know. 
 Ackley Improved chambers blow out the shoulder of the case to decrease body taper and increase shoulder angle, resulting in a higher case capacity. This will make a .30-06 shoot like a .300 Win. Mag. It is built on a Mauser Action which has had the "cock on open" conversion done and the rear sight milled off and tapped for a 1 piece base. It is fitted with a Military Barrel that was brand new for a .30 cal machine gun on an army tank. It started at 30" but has been cut down to 22" and reblued. I'm not sure what trigger was used but it feels light and crisp. It has a Leupold M8 6X which is a fixed 6 power. The stock has been bedded and is a nice piece of wood but does have some dings from over the years. 
 This gun has only had a couple of boxes of shells through it since it was built. It is a 1/2 MOA gun with good 168 gr. ammo. My dad's knees were bad and he never really got to hunt with it. He didn't even blow out enough cases to ever reload for it.

All and all this is a great rifle at a great price just in time for hunting season! $500 or best offer or $400 without the Leupold Scope.

The early 1873’s (up to 1877) had breech blocks case hardened and quenched in oil which gave them a black look. After 1877 case hardening process used water to quench which gave the brilliant silver color.

title: For Sale:  CZ-40B
postcontent:
CZ-40B, Case, Manual, Mag.Loader, 3 mags.  

This handgun began as a joint-venture between Colt and CZ, with Colt's one requirement being that the finished product must retain outward similarity to the 1911. However, any similarity between the 1911 and 40B end with the externals. In actually, the internal workings of the 40B are adapted from the CZ 75 line of pistols. The CZ 40B sports a lightweight alloy frame with an all steel slide. As opposed to the 1911 and most other western firearms, the 40B's slide rides inside the frame which helps to increase both reliability and accuracy. The standard magazines hold 10+1 rounds of .40 S&W in a double column design, although higher capacity aftermarket magazines for other CZ pistols are reported to function in the 40B. The pistol is finished with a black polymer coat which is supposed to be more durable than standard bluing during normal service usage.

U.S. Springfield Trapdoor Model 1884
45/70 cal

This is a beautiful firearm.  Gun has been sporterized some. Stock has been cut down from original length to carbine length. Barrel looks like it was blued at one time years ago. Some pitting but not very much. Gun is shootable (verified by Village Arms in Gap PA.

These sell unsporterized for $600-$1000, I’m asking $450. Will come with a padded transport sleeve.
